several different identifiers bic bic business identifier code also known as swift code or swift bic is a the mostly used international identifier of financial institutions swift is the registration authority for bics bics are used in financial transactions client and counterparty data bases compliance documents and many others a bic consists of eight or eleven characters comprising a financial institution code four characters a country code two characters a location code two characters and optionally a branch code three characters bic of jp morgan suisse sa and its components are shown in the table below bic  mgtcchggxxx bank bic code  mgtc country code  ch switzerland location code  gg branch code  xxx company registration number company registration number is a distinctive code issued upon registration of a new company this code can be used to find data about the company in a national company register company number  che european presence  banks in  countries this bank operates in the following european countries and selected dependent territories of the european countries belgium jp morgan europe ltd bruxelles  jp morgan international bank limited bruxelles  jpmorgan chase bank bruxelles cayman islands jp morgan trust company cayman limited grand cayman denmark jp morgan europe uk copenhagen branch filial af jp morgan europe limited storbritannien københavn v finland jp morgan europe limited helsingin sivuliike helsinki france jp morgan securities plc paris   jpmorgan chase bank national association paris  germany jp morgan ag frankfurt am main  jp morgan international bank limited frankfurt branch frankfurt am main  jp morgan securities plc frankfurt branch frankfurt am main ireland j p morgan bank dublin plc dublin  jp morgan bank ireland plc dublin italy jp morgan international bank limited milano  jp morgan securities plc milano  jpmorgan chase bank national association milano jersey jpmorgan chase bank na jersey branch st helier luxembourg jp morgan bank lu