 of the swiss market for jp morgan private bank based in geneva he leads a team of specialists that help individuals and organizations to optimize their fiscal arrangements and advises family owned businesses on how to protect their wealth for generations to come matteo also serves as a member of the jp morgan suisse management committee mr gianini joined jp morgan private bank in  after fourteen years at deutsche bank where he held various roles including his most recent role as head of wealth management in switzerland matteo held various client advisor roles in several banks prior to this he also holds a degree in economics and political sciences from the university of neuchatel davide lombardomanaging directorhead of investmentsdavide provides wealth management and investment advice for swissbased clients in geneva he works closely with clients to deliver strategic advice and holistic solutions for growing and preserving their wealth at the same time davide provides daily leadership and oversight to the entire team of swiss investment specialists before joining jp morgan private bank davide spent five years working in debt capital markets from london and as a hedge fund analyst at established european banks davide is a graduate of bocconi school of economics in milan philippe piedon‐lavauxexecutive directorwealth advisor philippe piedon‐lavaux is an executive director of jp morgan suisse sa and wealth advisor covering the swiss market as well as the uk resident non‐domiciled business in geneva prior to jp morgan mr piedon‐lavaux worked at the law firm scotto in geneva where he practiced three years as a senior lawyer in the wealth and tax planning team mr piedon‐lavaux started his career in paris with training as a french notary he then moved to the uk where he was  years at blake morgan one of uk’s leading full‐service law firms he was a partner in their private client department in london specializing in cross‐border and estate planning matters mr piedon‐lavaux has almost  years of experience in client estate and tax planning in switzerland france and the uk he holds the qualification as a french notary from the faculty of law at paris university and as a uk solicitor from bpp university college in london mr piedon‐lavaux is also a former honorary consul of france and has been giving lectures for various professional legal providers on estate planning topics for almost  years luc bachyexecutive directorsenior capital advisor luc is responsible for providing capital and credit advisory service to the firms clients in switzerland he advises on structures and terms for a wide range of complex customized solutions and partners with the integrated team to deliver optimal outcomes luc joined jp morgan private bank in  and was responsible for credit structuring for the french market followed by a year assignment in asia to develop the risk framework prior to joining jp morgan luc held a number of positions in hsbc investment banking in leveraged and acquisition finance and financing advisory luc is a graduate of parisdauphine university and escpeap